item.title: About Me
item.dc:creator: anyda
item.content:encoded:
Twelve years ago, I started working as a freelancer in my home country, creating WordPress websites.

Initially, I used pirated themes and made many mistakes, but I learned a lot. My sites and the server got hacked; then I knew how the hackers did it, how they entered and contaminated files, and how to delete or clean the mess.

Then, I started paying for theme licenses on Themeforest, and eventually, to cut costs and create more freely, I began using Hello Theme.

Since Elementor Pro is paid, I discovered PRO Elements, which is free. So, to this day, I still work with Hello + PRO Elements.

I always wanted to learn how to create my theme and have clean models for my clients, but I never did because I found it too complicated and ran out of time.

Being an intruder, I discovered how plugins work to be able to edit them.  I wanted to create one but perhaps needed more motivation. I also used hooks a lot, so I read a lot of WordPress documentation.

Now, studying at Georgian, I started making sites with HTML and Bootstrap, so combining Bootstrap with WordPress was more fun than I thought.

I have always been a self-learner, driven by curiosity and a desire to explore new things. Combining design and programming is my ultimate career path, and I am confident that I have made the right choice.

In my country, I studied programming, but it needed more design. Now, I have both design and programming and many years of experience, so when I finish my studies, I plan to start my small business here in Canada.

I completed my co-op with a company in Orillia, and based on my performance, I received recommendations from them to work with three more companies here in Canada. Along with my studies, I continue to work here and in my home country, where some clients still contact me or recommend me for work.

Creating a WordPress theme for the first time was a great experience. I am proud of this project.
